@node Introduction "AquaTopChat v1.0 Documentation"

Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
This door will time the "user - sysop" chats. When a chat is over, the
length of the chat is displayed and if it was long enough to be in the
toplist, the door says so and creates the top-chat bulletin. The bulletin
will also show two other records: the day with most chat time and the day
with most chats.
@endnode

@node Requirements "AquaTopChat v1.0 Documentation"

Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~
- An Amiga with OS 2.04 or higher.

- AmiExpress, SigmaExpress or any compatible program.
@endnode

@node Installation "AquaTopChat v1.0 Documentation"

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Just copy the 'AquaTopChat' directory (the inner one) from the archive to
'Doors:', and (for /X 3.0+) put the provided command icons
'ChatStart.info' and 'ChatEnd.info' in your 'SYSCmd' drawer.

Both AquaTopChatStart and AquaTopChatEnd are perfectly safe to make
resident.

You must edit your StartChat.txt(s) to contain the MCI command
'~CC_ChatStart'. Edit your EndChat.txt(s) to contain '~CC_ChatEnd'.

In case you didn't know: Any MCI text must start with a '~', and every MCI
command must end with a '|', a space (' ') or a newline!
@endnode

@node Configuration "AquaTopChat v1.0 Documentation"

Configuration
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
As configuration, AquaTopChat uses two environment variables:

1. 'AquaTopChat_Entries' - Determines the maximum number of chats to
                           include in the bulletin.  Default: '10'.

2. 'AquaTopChat_Bull'    - Determines the filename of the bulletin that
                           the door should create.
                           Default: 'Doors:AquaTopChat/AquaTopChat.bull'.

For example, if you want the bulletin to contain the 15 longest chats
instead of only 10, type 'SetEnv AquaTopChat_Entries 15' in a shell
window. To make it permanent type 'SetEnv ENVARC:AquaTopChat_Entries 15'
as well.
@endnode

@node History "AquaTopChat v1.0 Documentation"

History
~~~~~~~

0.1 (11-02-94) Started..

    (12-15-94) Made it residentable.

    (12-27-94) Worked on it alot..

    (12-31-94) Fixed a few bugs. Made the bulletin output.


0.2 (01-04-95) It now stores chat records (both time and #chats) and the
               dates they were set (the chat END date - it wouldn't work
               with start date).

               Had to change to format of the data file.

               Replaced some ANSI C functions with own ones/library
               functions. Exe-code decreased by ~1500 bytes.

               Polished the bulletin look. HH:MM time format, really
               centered texts.


1.0 (01-05-95) Discovered "AllocDosObject(DOS_FIB, TAG_DONE)" in the
               source instead of "AllocDosObjectTags(DOS_FIB, TAG_DONE)".
               (Not good..)

    (01-27-95) It now clears the unused part of the strings in the data
               file.

    (01-28-95) First public release!
@endnode

